  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Africa Renewable Energy Fund, L.P.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The AREF transaction is anticipated to have project-level impacts in the form of (i) improved services offerered to customers (i.e. increased access to energy); and (ii) environmental impacts that make a contribution to green industries (i.e. investments in clean energy with associated GHG emissions reductions).  

It will also have market-level impacts, (i) in sustainability, through an impact on building green industries; and (ii) on competitiveness, through diversification of the private equity product offerings in the market.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project is for an equity investment by the IFC Catalyst Fund in Africa Renewable Energy Fund (AREF or the Fund), a US$200 million, 10-year, 2014 vintage private equity fund focused on investments in renewable energy projects in Sub-Saharan Africa.</narrative>
  </description>
